ustry average Packaging Available in lightweight recycled glass, the revolutionary FrugalPac paper bottle, and the ultra-low waste, low carbon ecoSPIRITS platform Climate Positive Every bottle of Avallen removes more CO2 than it takes to produce thanks to the awesome apple trees Water Avallen only uses 1.2L of water to make per bottle which is 70-95% less than the industry average Packaging Available in lightweight recycled glass, the revolutionary FrugalPac paper bottle, and the ultra-low waste, low carbon ecoSPIRITS platform POSITIVE TO THE CORE We created Avallen with the belief that business can work in harmony with nature rather than against it and incorporate the lens of sustainability into every decision we make in the business, from who we bank with to what paper we print our event menus on. Learn More DOING IT FOR THE BEES Wild bee populations are in decline around the world, and if they disappear, our very survival as a species will be at risk. Without our furry little winged warriors, there''s no coffee. You can forget about pizza, and say goodbye to avocado on toast for breakfast. There would be no lemonade, no fries or potato chips. No berries, chillies, cucumbers, and, most importantly for us, no apples. And it''s not just the honey bee. We''re passionate about the bee''s that no one knows about, from the leafcutter bee to Wallace''s giant bee. Learn More FROM BLOSSOM TO BOTTLE Transparency and traceability are important words in any industry and they''re especially important when you''re putting something in your mouth. We work hard to provide evidence for everything we claim from publishing out LifeCycle Analysis and charitable donations to publishing our annual environmental impact. Learn More WE TRY TO BEE MORE We be(e)lieve that companies should be a force for good in the world so we try to bee more through sharing knowledge, inspiring others, and using our platform to champion positive change. We want to be the drink of choice for those fighting for our planet and all the beauty upon it. Learn More STEPH & TIM Take one part France, one part Colombia and one part England, shake and strain and you get Stephanie Jordan, Avallen''s queen bee Hailing from the golden beaches of Cornwall, a region that shares a long connection with Normandy, Tim Etherington-Judge has had an extremely successful career in drinks. Learn More Leafcutter Bee Leafcutter bees chew leaves or petals into fragments to build their nests, hence their common name. This is one of the largest genera of bees, with almost 1500 species OUR THOUGHTS & PARTNERSHIPS OUR THOUGHTS & PARTNERSHIPS News Blue Sky Thinking READ POST Environment A Christmas Letter from the Orchard  READ POST Leadership Pregnant in the Drinks Industry: A 2025 Reflection from Avallen Spirits Co-Founder READ POST

