INSERT INTO "public"."blog_posts" ("id", "title", "slug", "excerpt", "content", "featured_image_url", "author_id", "author_name", "tags", "content_type", "status", "published_at", "read_time", "view_count", "meta_title", "meta_description", "og_image_url", "created_at", "updated_at", "display_order") VALUES
	('205f804e-892b-4964-9dd7-6db47671dad8', 'The Planet Deserves Better Than A Pivot Table', 'better_than_a_pivot_table', 'I was tired of sustainability feeling like homework. After years in the drinks industry, I realised that saving the planet shouldn''t be the most boring part of my day. This is the story of why were ditching the messy spreadsheets and uninspiring tools to build something better, for drinks brands, for flavour, and for the soil. Discover why we believe the planet deserves better design, and how were making sustainability finally feel like a superpower.', '<p>When I co-founded Avallen Spirits with Stephanie Balmforth-Jordan all the way back in 2019 BC (before covid), we had a simple, singular ambition: to set new standards for sustainability in the spirits industry and put environmental impact front and centre of the conversation alongside delicious flavour. <br><br>I know it sounds clichd, but we genuinely wanted to build something that gave back more than it took, was climate positive, and supported the farmers, soil, and bees that are critical architects of the final product. <br><br>The sustainability side of it was my bag, Stephanie is the brilliant business woman with proud French heritage, endless connections, and boundless determination who made Avallen commercially successful. <br></p><img class="max-w-full h-auto rounded-lg" src="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/scl/fi/an2fxe60hbdlsik4zyf89/Facebook-banner_v02-03.jpg?rlkey=jamrqc4rj68fs6g0jd0yuq6iz&amp;st=o0yaa4ak&amp;dl=0&amp;raw=1"><p><br></p><p>Growing up on the beaches of Cornwall, the most beautiful part of the UK with palm trees in the garden, miles of golden sand, and one of the only regions in the world that is both temperate and subtropical, it''s hard not to fall in love with nature.<br><br>Not only do I love the challenge of building businesses that put planet and people alongside profit, I believe it should be the only way to do business. The time worn mantra of ''leave it better than you found it'' rings loudly in my head. <br></p><p>While my dreams were of building sustainable businesses, I didnt spend my time dreaming about being chained to the laptop, buried in messy spreadsheets, searching through emails, writing reports that hardly anyone read, bothering people for utilities data, and losing sleep over whether a single miscalculation would lead to a "greenwashing" headline and losing the trust of people we''d worked so hard to build.<br></p><p>At times sustainability felt like homework rather than what got me out of bed in the morning. It was uninspiring, administrative, expensive, and frankly, a bit of a bore.<br></p><img class="max-w-full h-auto rounded-lg" src="https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/pzdrr4rslv-1767699349502.jpg"><p></p><p><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><br><strong>The Sustainability Paralysis</strong><br></span></p><p>After launching Avallen and getting a lot of recognition for our sustainability work, we launched a consultancy Avallen Solutions 2024. The goal was to help other drinks brands with their sustainability journey, sharing the knowledge and experience we had learned along the way, for the greater good of both the industry and our planet. <br><br>Whether I was talking to a globally recognised island rum brand or a genre defining non-alc aperitif, the story was often the same: people wanted to do the right thing, but they were stuck in what I like to call "Sustainability Paralysis."<br></p><p>The tools are available and they do what they say on the tin, but none of them are purpose built for the industry. You either pay a small fortune, for a start-up drinks brand at least, for an expert to write a report that sits in a drawer, or you use an expensive off the shelf carbon calculator (we did for Avallen) that only reports your GHG emissions but doesn''t help you measure your water impact, B Corp ambitions, or risk of being fined for greenwashing.<br></p><p>The industry we love is entirely reliant on a healthy planet, and as I like to say, flavour starts in the soil. Our liquid is, quite literally, on loan from nature, and the planet deserves better than a pivot table in Excel.<br></p><p></p><h3><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><strong>An SOS For Drinks</strong></span><br></h3><p></p><p>I built alka<strong>tera</strong> to be the platform I wish Id had on day one at Avallen, and much more.<br></p><p>I built Alkatera to be the <strong>Sustainability Operating System</strong> for the drinks industry and to make the complex simple. It''s more than just a carbon calculator, it''s the one platform to rule them all (die hard LOTR fan here) when it comes to sustainability in drinks, covering everything from emissions and circularity to supply chain impact and risk assessment for greenwashing.<br><br><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><strong>Alka-</strong></span>: drawn from <strong>Alchemy</strong> and the historic roots of <strong>Alcohol</strong> production. It represents the "liquid craft" of our industry. <br></p><ol><li><p><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><strong>-Tera</strong>:</span> This is a direct reference to <strong>Terra</strong> (Earth/Soil). As we say in our manifesto, <em>"The soil does not negotiate."</em> It represents the agricultural foundation of every drink and our commitment to protecting the ecosystems that yield our ingredients.<br><br>Weve taken the jargon-heavy science of sustainability and automated the calculations, wrapping it in a design that (hopefully) is a joy to use.<br><br>We are moving away from a traditional consultancy model making do with tools that don''t quite fit because advice isn''t enough anymore. In a world of tightening regulations, increasing reporting demands, and the EU Green Claims Directive, drinks brands dont just need an idea and a roadmap, they need an engine. <br><br></p><img class="max-w-full h-auto rounded-lg" src="https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/s3ipxcn2fpc-1767699242713.jpg"><p></p></li></ol><p></p><h3><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><strong>Our Philosophy: Sustainability, Distilled</strong><br></span></h3><p>We have a few core beliefs that drive everything we do at alka<strong>tera</strong>:<br></p><ul><li><p><strong>Design is a Function:</strong> If a tool is beautiful and intuitive, people will use it. If its clunky, itll be frustrating and used less. Having studied design at university, I truly believe that it can be the bridge between data and action.<br></p></li><li><p><strong>The "Glass Box" Standard:</strong> No more hidden math, misleading numbers, or obscure claims. Every calculation in Alkatera is transparent and traceable, placed inside a digital glassbox that can''t be broken, altered, or edited. Trust is earned through data, not promises.<br></p></li><li><p><strong>Sustainability is a Growth Lever:</strong> This isnt about "checking a box" for compliance or reporting because you have to. Its about building brands that are built for the long game, resilient, audit-ready, and commercially attractive to distributors, wholesalers, customers, citizens, and investors.<br></p></li></ul><h3><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><strong>Whats Next?</strong></span></h3><p>We are currently in our final build phase, working with a founding cohort of brands to ensure every feature solves a real-world problem and the platform is ready for launch with rigorously tested calculations, a suite of useful tools, and a robust plan for development.<br></p><p>We launch in early <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><strong>February 2026</strong>.</span><br></p><p>Alkatera is our antidote to sustainability apathy. Were here to demystify the science, lighten the administrative load, and help you focus on what you do best: making incredible drinks.<br></p><p>The soil does not negotiate, but with the right tools, we can ensure were in harmony with it for generations to come.<br></p><p></p><p><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><strong>Welcome to the journey.</strong></span></p>', 'https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/z17mcsom8yk-1767699538820.png', '27ea31a3-949c-4107-bcd1-e1b1eff818d1', 'hello', '{Strategy,Sustainability,"Drinks Industry",Business}', 'article', 'published', '2026-01-06 11:54:43.097+00', '5 min read', 5, 'The Planet Deserves Better Than A Pivot Table', 'Discover why were building alkatera: the sustainability operating system for drinks brands. Were replacing spreadsheets with clarity. Sustainability, Simplified', 'https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/z17mcsom8yk-1767699538820.png', '2026-01-06 11:54:43.359774+00', '2026-01-06 15:24:25.860669+00', 0),
	('adb3d307-2abd-4b99-bd0f-2538138314b1', 'The Sustainability Operating System for Drinks', 'the-sustainability-operating-system-for-drinks', 'Ever wondered what a ''sustainability operating system'' actually does? Its more than just a buzzword. From our signature digital ''Glass Box'' concept to tracking the four pillars of real impact: carbon, water, waste, and land. Our founder pulls back the curtain on alkatera. Discover how were replacing messy spreadsheets with strategic clarity, helping drinks brands move from compliance fatigue to genuine growth. Built by the industry, for the industry. Its time for sustainability, distilled.', '<p>Now that you''ve (hopefully) seen <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span><strong>, </strong>you might be thinking, nice branding, but what exactly is a ''<em>sustainability operating system</em>'' anyway and what on earth do they actually do. <br><br>Is it just another startup looking to take some money from me to solve a problem that I didn''t know existed, or can they actually help me and is it good value for money.<br><br>Having co-founded <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="text-[#ccff00] underline" href="https://avallenspirits.com">Avallen Spirits</a> in 2019 I''m all too aware of the huge amount of admin, and guess, work required to both sustainability into a drinks brand, the increasing reporting and legislation requirements on all companies, and a growing distrust from citizens in products claims combined with a growing desire to purchase sustainable brands. <br><br>I''m building <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span> to be the ''all in one'' platform for all your sustainability needs, from carbon calculation and water measurement to greenwashing risk assessment and B Corp Certification support.</p><ul><li><p>No longer will your data be sprawled across multiple spreadsheets, buried in the dark depths of your inbox, or stuck with a supplier that doesn''t reply to your emails.</p><img class="max-w-full h-auto rounded-lg" src="https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/citk3vjx6y5-1768300152762.jpg"></li></ul><ul><li><p><em>But Tim, you still haven''t answered ''what exactly does </em><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><em>alka</em><strong><em>tera</em></strong></span><em> do?''</em><br><br>To explain exactly what <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span> does, I want to go back to the very first aspect of the platform that I built and what every calculation and point of data relies upon. I''m going to try and not get too technical and explain it so that ''me from 1 year ago when I knew nothing about coding'' can understand.<br><br>Trust, transparency, and auditability are all critical words in both business and sustainability. <br><br>The method we built at <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span> is a digital ''glass box''. An unbreakable, uneditable, undeletable box into which we place the data, methodology, and calculations, along with a unique ID number, the organisation and user number, and a time stamp. <br><br>This ''glass box'' means that all calculations and data entry points in <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span> are completely transparent, tagged, and easily available for audit. <br><br>It''s this critical principle that builds trust and transparency that our entire platform is built on.</p><img class="max-w-full h-auto rounded-lg" src="https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/fvqfzecfbf-1768299449517.jpg"></li></ul><p>I spent almost all of my career in drinks. You could, if you wanted to make me feel old, call me a veteran after decades of being behind the bar slinging cocktails in world class bars, working at Diageo with some of the most globally recognised spirits brands in the world, or co-founding my own sustainably focus brand Avallen Calvados.</p><p>It''s fair to say that I have a fairly decent understanding of drinks and the specific needs, wants, and pain points of the industry.</p><ul><li><p><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span> is built on the back of this understanding and designed to be the only tool you need for all your sustainability work. Whether it''s connecting up your supply chain for an accurate impact picture, or using our ''sandbox'' feature so you can see the impacts of changing your bottle or supply to aid with decision making, everything we built is to help you and your brand improve, grow, and grasp the commercial opportunities.</p><img class="max-w-full h-auto rounded-lg" src="https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/u1mmehqljmf-1768299485410.png"><p>Everything starts in the soil and the clouds. Our products are made from natures outputs and our most used ingredient is water. <br><br>So just tracking your carbon emissions misses the biggest part of the picture. <br><br>At <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span> we track 4 critical categories: Greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions, water, waste &amp; circularity, and land &amp; biodiversity impact. <br><br>Each metric has a key role.<br><br>GHG emissions impact climate change, which is the biggest threat to our industry due to its disruption of agriculture and economies. <br><br>Water is our most commonly used and important ingredient. It''s availability is becoming increasingly unpredictable from multi-year droughts to catastrophic floods. <br><br>Waste &amp; Circularity leans into both our packaging design and ingredient use, reporting accurate measurements which can be used as a platform for improvement and cost savings.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>And because all our products start their lives in the soil, it''s absolutely critical that we measure and reduce our impact on the land and biodiversity through land use, eutrophication, acidification, and biodiversity loss. <br><br>Building <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span> around these 4 categories ensures that we are helping brands, and the wider industry, survive and thrive for the long term, not just until the next reporting period.<br><br>Data is valueless unless it''s used effectively to drive meaningful change. In a time where we''re flooded with data, there''s absolutely no point spending time, and money, collecting more of it if it''s not going to positively impact your business. <br><br><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span> takes the data you input and turns it into valuable, easy to understand outputs that you can then use as part of your strategic planning as well as track your progress over time. <br><br>The platform can also help you manage the ever growing compliance and reporting requirements. No longer will you have to spend valuable time and resources gathering the data and writing sustainability reports. We collate the data, formulate it into a compelling narrative, leaving you to add the personalised finishing touches of storytelling and design. <br><br>And we''ve got you covered to navigate the new anti-greenwashing legislation coming in with both verifiable, auditable data as rock solid proof to any claims you make, but also a greenwash risk assessment tool that flags any potential risk before you publish.<br><br>We''re launching in early February 2026 at a special ''Founding Members'' price, so if you want to find out more, have a demo of the platform to see if in action, or sign up and get on board, then click the ''<a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="text-[#ccff00] underline" href="https://alkatera.com/contact"><strong>Get Access</strong></a>'' button and we''ll be in touch.</p></li></ul><h3>Only a few weeks until we go live and I couldn''t be more excited if I tried. <br><br>Much love, Tim</h3><p></p>', 'https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/hnzxad162xq-1768299918694.jpg', '27ea31a3-949c-4107-bcd1-e1b1eff818d1', 'hello', '{alkatera,sustainability,business}', 'article', 'published', '2026-01-13 10:25:45.017+00', '5 min read', 19, 'The Sustainability Operating System for Drinks', 'Stop drowning in spreadsheets. alkatera founder Tim explains how alkatera helps drinks brands measure impact, ensure compliance, and grow. Sustainability, Distilled.', 'https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/hnzxad162xq-1768299918694.jpg', '2026-01-13 10:25:45.295343+00', '2026-01-13 20:43:54.564617+00', 0),
	('ef5e09cb-9581-48e2-b5d5-0ab8e46eafdc', 'The Era of Greenwashing Is Over', 'the_era_of_greenwashing_is_over', '"The days of greenwashing are officially over. With the Green Claims Code and DMCC regulations taking the gloves off, sustainability is no longer just about the planet, its about business opportunity. Tim explains how Alkatera turns compliance from a risk into your strongest competitive advantage, ensuring you win the shelf in 2026.', '<p>Post #3, which means we''re getting close to launch as this is my penultimate writings before I click the button to make the <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span><strong> </strong>platform live. I am more excited about this launch than anything I''ve done before, but also more nervous about its succes. <br><br>In my last post, I focused on the ''what'' and pulled back the curtain on our Glass Box concept, the engine inside <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span> that ensures your data is unbreakable, uneditable, and completely transparent. Beyond all the features, calculations, and fancy visualisations, this is the most important feature of the platform.</p><p>But I can hear some of you asking (I know because I''ve been trying to convince people about sustainability in drinks for a while now): <em>That sounds clever, Tim, but do I really need a some fancy digital technology just to sell a bottle of gin?</em></p><p>Five years ago? Maybe not. You could slap a green leaf on your label, say that your plastic bottle is recyclable, talk about natural botanicals, tell the world you''re ''eco-friendly'' and pretty much say what you want.</p><p>Not only does that not work any more as citizens are a lot more savvy to seeing through greenwashing, we are entering an era of radical accountability for sustainability in business. <br><br>And for us lovely people in the drinks industry, the days of "Trust Me, Bro" and "Eco-Friendly" marketing are officially over.</p><img class="max-w-full h-auto rounded-lg" src="https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/ab5c2il5nm-1768857646982.jpg"><h3><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><strong>The Greenwashing Trap</strong></span></h3><p>We all know the industry is scared, and not just of more taxes, Meta''s new of the rules around advertising, and changes in drinking habits. I speak to founders every week who are worried being caught greenwashing. So much so that we have a new term: <strong>Greenhushing, </strong><br>aka brands that are doing good work but are too terrified to talk about it for fear of getting the wording wrong.</p><p>Regulators across the UK and EU are taking the gloves off. The Green Claims Code isnt a suggestion anymore; its the rulebook enforced by the DMCC (I thought I''d escaped the life of acronyms when I left Diageo!). <br><br>If you say your vodka is "planet-friendly" you need extraordinary proof, claiming you''re carbon neutral through offsetting is out, and traceable data to back it up is in. You aren''t just risking a slap on the wrist anymore, youre risking fines (upto 10% of global revenue in extreme cases), product recalls to change labels, and a potential PR disaster that destroys trust that can take years to rebuild.</p><p>This is where <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span> changes the game.</p><img class="max-w-full h-auto rounded-lg" src="https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/3d7ejjkjtnw-1768857346570.png"><h3><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><strong>Turn Compliance into Confidence</strong></span></h3><p>I built <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span> to be your proverbial digital shield. Our ''Glass Box'' foundation gives you the confidence that any claims you make using data on our platform is transparent, auditable, and defensible against any claim.</p><p>I built an Anti-Greenwash risk assessment tool called ''<strong>Greenwash Guardian</strong>'' (too many Marvel films?). it stress-tests your marketing against the latest UK and European legislation. Before you print that new label, update your website, or publish that Instagram post, <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span> verifies your claim against your live Glass Box data and gives you a full risk assessment.</p><p>It means you can go to market with your chest out, knowing that if a regulator (or a cynical customer) asks "Prove it," you can pull up the data instantly.</p><img class="max-w-full h-auto rounded-lg" src="https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/2dj8t15j4dr-1768857473212.jpg"><h3><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><strong>Winning the Shelf</strong></span></h3><p>But lets move beyond fear, there''s enough of that in the world today.</p><p>Sustainability is no longer just about saving the planet; its about winning that tender, securing distribution, and catching the eye of increasingly demand citizens.</p><p>Whether youre pitching to a major supermarket, a global hotel group, a new distributor in Dubai, or an independent retailer, the questions are changing. Increasingly buyers dont just want to taste the liquid; they want to see your carbon footprint, your water usage, and your supply chain ethics. They are being asked for this information under new legislation, and they''re starting to ask their suppliers for it too.</p><p>Ive sat in those meetings with Avallen. Even tho we built that brand from the ground up to be as sustainable as possible, I still remember the feeling of scrambling to find answers in a spreadsheet while a buyer waited.</p><p>With <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span>, you stop scrambling. You input the data and we use technology to provide standardised, verifiable reports from a single source of truth that make you look like the most professional brand in the room, turning sustainability into a competitive advantage that wins you listings.</p><img class="max-w-full h-auto rounded-lg" src="https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/ol02kseqwts-1768857726159.jpg"><h3><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><strong>The Bottom Line</strong></span></h3><p>I didnt build <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);">alka<strong>tera</strong></span> just to make you feel good about the environment or to bolster my CV. I built it to make your business robust, compliant, and ready for the future as well as ensure the long term health of the industry we both love.</p><p>The drinks industry is changing, in more ways than we can cope with sometimes. The brands that win in 2026 won''t just be the ones with the best liquid; theyll be the ones with the best data.</p><p><span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><strong>We launch in two weeks.</strong></span></p><p>If you want to secure your brands future and stop worrying about what you can and cant say, its time to get on board.</p><p>Click the <span style="color: rgb(204, 255, 0);"><strong>Get Access</strong></span> button up in the top right-hand corner of your screen to join the waitlist and take advantage of our ''Founding Partners'' pricing.</p><p>Much love, Tim</p>', 'https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/jiddma4b9pg-1768857207828.jpg', '266a09aa-b7aa-4530-80d2-597be1eb23d9', 'Tim Etherington-Judge', '{Greenwashing,Sustainability,Business}', 'article', 'published', '2026-01-19 21:22:20.399+00', '5 min read', 29, 'greenwashing_is_over', 'The days of greenwashing are over. Learn how Alkatera turns Green Claims Code compliance into a competitive advantage to help you win the shelf in 2026.', 'https://dfcezkyaejrxmbwunhry.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/jiddma4b9pg-1768857207828.jpg', '2026-01-19 21:22:20.737663+00', '2026-01-20 09:02:34.00836+00', 0);
