angipane Rich, fruity and nutty spritz. YOU NEED 45ml Avallen calvados15ml almond orgeat15ml lemon juice1 dash orange bittersSparkling wine METHOD Shake all ingredients except bubbles in a cocktail shaker with ice. Double strain into a coupette and top with the bubbles. GLASS Coupette GARNISH Orange zest Grab Ingredients Now > Angel Face Another co-founder favourite Another co-founder favourite Angel Face Another co-founder favourite YOU NEED 30ml Avallen calvados30ml London dry gin15ml apricot liqueur METHOD In a mixing tin/mixing glass, stir all ingredients over ice. Strain into a chilled glass. GLASS Nic n nora or small rocks GARNISH Orange zest, discarded Grab Ingredients Now > Avallen Espresso Our espresso martini Our espresso martini Avallen Espresso Our espresso martini YOU NEED 40ml Avallen calvados15ml coffee liqueur30ml fresh espresso10ml sugar syrup METHOD Combine all ingredients in a cocktail shaker and shake with ice. Double strain into a coupette. GLASS Coupette GARNISH 3 coffee beans Grab Ingredients Now > Orchard View Boozy, sweet & squarely delicious Boozy, sweet & squarely delicious Orchard View Boozy, sweet & squarely delicious YOU NEED 25ml Avallen calvados25ml rye whiskey20ml sweet vermouth5ml DOM Benedictine2 dashes Peychauds bitters2 dashes Angostura bitters METHOD Stir all ingredients in a mixing glass and strain into a glass over ice. GLASS Small rocks GARNISH Lemon twist Grab Ingredients Now > Calvados Sazerac Our Co-founders favourite classic Our Co-founders favourite classic Calvados Sazerac Our Co-founders favourite classic YOU NEED 30ml Avallen calvados30ml rye whiskey5ml sugar syrup4 dashes Peychauds bitters1 dash Angostura bittersAbsinthe rinse METHOD Rinse glass with absinthe, stir other ingredients in a mixing glass and pour into the rinsed glass. GLASS Nic n Nora or small rocks GARNISH Lemon zest then discard Grab Ingredients Now > Delicious Sour OG calvados classic from 1893 OG calvados classic from 1893 Delicious Sour OG calvados classic from 1893 YOU NEED 45ml Avallen calvados10ml crme de pche20ml fresh lemon juice15ml sugar syrup3 dashes cocktail foamer METHOD Add ingredients into a shaker and dry shake to activate foamer. Open shaker, add ice and shake hard. Double strain into a coupette. GLASS Coupette GARNISH Dehydrated apple slice Grab Ingredients Now > Pan American Clipper Tart and refreshing. Ooooh! Tart and refreshing. Ooooh! Pan American Clipper Tart and refreshing. Ooooh! YOU NEED 60ml Avallen calvados20ml fresh lime juice20ml grenadine3 dashes absinthe METHOD Shake all ingredients with ice and strain into a chilled glass GLASS Coupette GARNISH Peace and love Grab Ingredients Now > Shrill Carder Bee Shrill carders are one of the rarest, and smallest, of all bumble bees, and they get their name from their distinctive high-pitch buzz GRAB A BOTTLE OF AVALLEN FROM BLOSSOM TO BOTTLE FROM BLOSSOM TO BOTTLE The Best Orchards Every drop of Avallen begins its journey in the traditional apple orchards of Normandy, France, within 30km of the distillery. Harvest Time Our apples come from over 200 individual orchards, supporting the local community and biodiversity of the region. Apple Processing The apples are delivered, washed, chopped, juiced, and left to ferment outside for a completely natural wild fermentation. Distilling & Aging Distillation happens on a column still before our precious liquid is transferred to French oak casks for 2-3 years. It is then carefully blended, finally becoming our delicious calvados. Packaging Avallen is bottled by our lovely worker bees and packed into unbleached boxes, ready to be shipped around the world and enjoyed. Honey Bee The western honey bee was one of the first domesticated insects, and with human assistance, now occupies every continent except Antartica. learn more about avallen MORE THAN JUST A DRINK MORE THAN JUST A DRINK MORE THAN JUST A DRINK All companies environmental impact goes far beyond the products they make. Climate Positive Every bottle of Avallen removes more CO2 than it takes to produce thanks to the awesome apple trees Water Avallen only uses 1.2L of water to make per bottle which is 70-95% less than the industry average Packaging Available in lightweight recycled glass, the revolutionary FrugalPac paper bottle, and the ultra-low waste, low carbon ecoSPIRITS platform Climate Positive Every bottle of Avallen removes more CO2 than it takes to produce thanks to the awesome apple trees Water Avallen only uses 1.2L of water to make per bottle which is 70-95% less than the industry average Packaging Available in lightweight recycled glass, the revolutionary FrugalPac paper bottle, and the ultra-low waste, low carbon ecoSPIRITS platform POSITIVE TO THE CORE We created Avallen with the belief that business can work in harmony with nature rather than against it and incorporate the lens of sustainability into every decision we make in the business, from who we bank with to what paper we print our event menus on. Learn More DOING IT FOR THE BEES Wild bee populations are in decline around the world, and if they disappear, our very survival as a species will be at risk. Without our furry little winged warriors, there''s no coffee. You can forget about pizza, and say goodbye to avocado on toast for breakfast. There would be no lemonade, no fries or potato chips. No berries, chillies, cucumbers, and, most importantly for us, no apples. And it''s not just the honey bee. We''re passionate about the bee''s that no one knows about, from the leafcutter bee to Wallace''s giant bee. Learn More FROM BLOSSOM TO BOTTLE Transparency and traceability are important words in any industry and they''re especially important when you''re putting something in your mouth. We work hard to provide evidence for everything we claim from publishing out LifeCycle Analysis and charitable donations to publishing our annual environmental impact. Learn More WE TRY TO BEE MORE We be(e)lieve that companies should be a force for good in the world so we try to bee more through sharing knowledge, inspiring others, and using our platform to champion positive change. We want to be the drink of choice for those fighting for our planet and all the beauty upon it. Learn More STEPH & TIM Take one part France, one part Colombia and one part England, shake and strain and you get Stephanie Jordan, Avallen''s queen bee Hailing from the golden beaches of Cornwall, a region that shares a long connection with Normandy, Tim Etherington-Judge has had an extremely successful career in drinks. Learn More Leafcutter Bee Leafcutter bees chew leaves or petals into fragments to build their nests, hence their common name. This is one of the largest genera of bees, with almost 1500 species OUR THOUGHTS & PARTNERSHIPS OUR THOUGHTS & PARTNERSHIPS News Blue Sky Thinking READ POST Environment A Christmas Letter from the Orchard  READ POST Leadership Pregnant in the Drinks Industry: A 2025 Reflection from Avallen Spirits Co-Founder READ POST
INSERT INTO "public"."greenwash_assessment_claims" ("id", "assessment_id", "claim_text", "claim_context", "risk_level", "risk_score", "issue_type", "issue_description", "legislation_name", "legislation_article", "legislation_jurisdiction", "suggestion", "suggested_revision", "display_order", "created_at") VALUES
	('9bc38dca-e666-4126-8f33-11eeafb254dc', '09952926-3203-4c13-bd27-bdd352d0fa69', 'Climate Positive Calvados', 'Title and Description', 'medium', 65, 'vague_claim', 'The term ''climate positive'' is a strong claim that requires robust substantiation. It''s not immediately clear what the scope of this claim is (e.g., cradle-to-gate, cradle-to-grave). Consumers may misunderstand the extent of the positive impact.', 'Green Claims Code (CMA, 2021)', 'Principle 1: Claims must be truthful and accurate; Principle 6: Claims must be substantiated', 'uk', 'Provide a clear and concise explanation of how the product achieves climate positivity, including the methodology used to calculate the carbon footprint and the offsetting or sequestration activities involved.', 'Avallen Calvados: Climate Positive through [Specific Actions, e.g., Apple Tree Carbon Sequestration and Reduced Packaging Emissions]. See our LCA report for details.', 0, '2026-01-29 07:46:57.119382+00'),
	('3dd94783-6a3d-4488-b11d-14848fcc86a8', '09952926-3203-4c13-bd27-bdd352d0fa69', 'Avallen calvados is a climate positive spirit made from just three things: Apples, Water, and Time.', 'Description of the product', 'medium', 50, 'unsubstantiated', 'While the simplicity of ingredients is appealing, it doesn''t automatically equate to climate positivity. The claim needs to be backed by data showing that the production process, including apple farming, distillation, and packaging, results in a net removal of CO2 from the atmosphere.', 'Green Claims Code (CMA, 2021)', 'Principle 6: Claims must be substantiated', 'uk', 'Link to a publicly available lifecycle assessment (LCA) or carbon footprint analysis that supports the claim. Quantify the carbon emissions and removals associated with each stage of the product''s lifecycle.', 'Avallen Calvados: Made with Apples, Water, and Time. Our carbon footprint is offset by apple tree sequestration, making us climate positive. [Link to LCA]', 1, '2026-01-29 07:46:57.119382+00'),
	('45c0f81c-ab2a-4b9b-8560-6d9c01aecd6b', '09952926-3203-4c13-bd27-bdd352d0fa69', 'Our Mission It is our ambition to become one of the world''s most sustainable spirits', 'Company mission statement', 'medium', 45, 'vague_claim', 'The term ''sustainable'' is generic and lacks specific meaning. It''s unclear what specific environmental or social criteria the company is using to define sustainability.', 'Directive on Empowering Consumers for the Green Transition (2024/825)', 'Article related to banning generic environmental claims', 'eu', 'Replace ''sustainable'' with specific, measurable, achievable, relevant, and time-bound (SMART) goals. For example, ''Reduce water consumption by 20% by 2025''.', 'Our Mission: To reduce our carbon footprint by 30% by 2030 and source 100% of our packaging from recycled materials.', 2, '2026-01-29 07:46:57.119382+00'),
	('59d5fbf3-a673-47da-b76d-b9f70e33c5b7', '09952926-3203-4c13-bd27-bdd352d0fa69', 'Water Avallen only uses 1.2L of water to make per bottle which is 70-95% less than the industry average', 'Environmental impact section', 'medium', 60, 'misleading_comparison', 'While the water usage is impressive, the claim relies on a comparison to an ''industry average''. It''s important to clarify which industry average is being used, the source of the data, and whether the comparison is truly fair and representative.', 'Green Claims Code (CMA, 2021)', 'Principle 4: Comparisons must be fair and meaningful', 'uk', 'Provide the source of the industry average data and specify the scope of the comparison (e.g., ''compared to the average water usage of spirits production in Europe'').', 'Water Usage: We use only 1.2L of water per bottle, 70-95% less than the European spirits industry average (source: [Insert Source]).', 3, '2026-01-29 07:46:57.119382+00'),
	('79aa315d-fecd-43b9-97b1-f2289b2e970a', '09952926-3203-4c13-bd27-bdd352d0fa69', 'Every bottle of Avallen removes more CO2 than it takes to produce thanks to the awesome apple trees', 'Environmental impact section', 'medium', 70, 'unsubstantiated', 'This is a strong claim that needs to be backed by a full lifecycle assessment. The claim needs to account for all emissions associated with the production, distribution, and disposal of the product. The carbon sequestration of the apple trees needs to be accurately quantified and verified.', 'Green Claims Code (CMA, 2021)', 'Principle 6: Claims must be substantiated', 'uk', 'Provide a link to a detailed lifecycle assessment (LCA) that outlines the methodology, data sources, and assumptions used to calculate the carbon footprint and sequestration. Ensure the LCA is conducted by a reputable third party.', 'Our apple trees sequester more carbon than we emit in production, making each bottle climate positive. See our LCA report for details: [Link to LCA]', 4, '2026-01-29 07:46:57.119382+00'),
	('4c501d75-a45a-40f9-b692-a95a9b81ca4b', '53500dff-7db0-471d-a1c1-7e9ea0499355', 'Climate Positive Calvados', 'Title and repeated throughout the content', 'high', 75, 'unsubstantiated', 'While the company states that apple trees sequester more carbon than they emit, this needs to be thoroughly substantiated with a full lifecycle assessment, including all aspects of production, packaging, and distribution. The term ''climate positive'' can be misleading if the positive impact is not significant or is offset by other negative impacts.', 'Green Claims Code', 'Principle 6: Claims must be substantiated', 'uk', 'Provide a detailed lifecycle assessment demonstrating the climate positive impact, including specific data and methodology. Be transparent about the scope and limitations of the assessment.', 'Consider rewording to ''Calvados with a climate positive impact through apple tree carbon sequestration'' and link to the LCA.', 0, '2026-01-29 07:49:08.099289+00'),
	('01fea712-e2c6-472f-affe-78be59e3a7da', '53500dff-7db0-471d-a1c1-7e9ea0499355', 'Avallen calvados is a climate positive spirit made from just three things: Apples, Water, and Time.', 'Description of the product', 'medium', 60, 'hidden_tradeoff', 'While highlighting the natural ingredients, this claim may distract from other environmental impacts associated with the production and distribution of spirits, such as energy consumption, packaging, and transportation. Focusing solely on the ingredients creates a potentially misleading impression of overall environmental friendliness.', 'Green Claims Code', 'Principle 3: Claims must not omit or hide important information', 'uk', 'Acknowledge and address other environmental impacts beyond the ingredients, such as packaging and transportation. Provide information on efforts to mitigate these impacts.', 'Consider adding a sentence acknowledging other environmental considerations: ''Made with apples, water, and time, we are also committed to minimizing our impact through sustainable packaging and responsible sourcing.''', 1, '2026-01-29 07:49:08.099289+00'),
	('31beb147-e223-4bff-a155-d323bc0fb380', '53500dff-7db0-471d-a1c1-7e9ea0499355', 'Our Mission It is our ambition to become one of the world''s most sustainable spirits', 'Company mission statement', 'medium', 50, 'future_promise', 'This is a future promise without specific, measurable, achievable, relevant, and time-bound (SMART) goals. It lacks concrete commitments and a clear timeline, making it difficult to verify progress and potentially misleading.', 'Green Claims Code', 'Principle 1: Claims must be truthful and accurate', 'uk', 'Replace the general statement with specific, measurable sustainability goals and a timeline for achieving them. For example, ''Our mission is to reduce our carbon footprint by 20% by 2027 through [specific actions].''', 'Replace with specific, measurable goals: ''Our mission is to reduce our carbon footprint by 20% by 2027 through sustainable packaging and renewable energy.''', 2, '2026-01-29 07:49:08.099289+00'),
	('1c381175-6209-46b7-be16-b5942eb50948', 'ac83dd81-6206-46e8-93d3-c95290082bf4', 'carbon neutral by 2030', 'Our company is committed to being 100% eco-friendly and carbon neutral by 2030.', 'medium', 65, 'future_promise', 'While a commitment to carbon neutrality is positive, the claim lacks detail on how this will be achieved and verified. It is a future promise without concrete steps.', 'Green Claims Code', 'Principle 6: Claims must be substantiated', 'uk', 'Provide a detailed plan outlining the steps to achieve carbon neutrality, including specific targets and timelines.', 'Our company is committed to achieving carbon neutrality by 2030 through a combination of energy efficiency improvements, renewable energy investments, and verified carbon offsetting projects.', 1, '2026-01-29 12:57:34.45762+00'),
	('92a8e780-88ba-4194-8fa8-c9711d4f3533', '53500dff-7db0-471d-a1c1-7e9ea0499355', 'Available in lightweight recycled glass, the revolutionary FrugalPac paper bottle, and the ultra-low waste, low carbon ecoSPIRITS platform', 'Description of packaging options', 'low', 30, 'misleading_comparison', 'While highlighting the availability of more sustainable packaging options is positive, the claim of ''ultra-low waste, low carbon'' for ecoSPIRITS needs to be substantiated with data and compared fairly against other packaging options. Consumers need to understand the context of these claims.', 'Green Claims Code', 'Principle 4: Comparisons must be fair and meaningful', 'uk', 'Provide specific data on the carbon footprint and waste reduction associated with each packaging option, including a comparison to standard packaging methods. Ensure the comparison is fair and transparent.', 'Add data points: ''Available in lightweight recycled glass (65% recycled content), the revolutionary FrugalPac paper bottle (1/6 the carbon footprint of glass), and the ecoSPIRITS platform (reduces carbon emissions by X% compared to single-use bottles).''', 3, '2026-01-29 07:49:08.099289+00'),
	('d369da28-abb3-458e-819d-9854d7a52e4e', '53500dff-7db0-471d-a1c1-7e9ea0499355', 'We created Avallen with the belief that business can work in harmony with nature rather than against it and incorporate the lens of sustainability into every decision we make in the business, from who we bank with to what paper we print our event menus on.', 'Statement of company philosophy', 'low', 25, 'vague_claim', 'While the sentiment is positive, the claim is vague and lacks specific details about how sustainability is integrated into every decision. It''s difficult for consumers to verify the extent of this commitment.', 'Directive on Empowering Consumers for the Green Transition (2024/825)', 'Article 3: Prohibition of generic environmental claims', 'eu', 'Provide specific examples of sustainable practices implemented in different areas of the business, such as banking, sourcing, and operations. Quantify the impact of these practices where possible.', 'Add examples: ''We integrate sustainability into every decision, from banking with Triodos to using recycled paper for our menus, reducing our environmental impact by X%.''', 4, '2026-01-29 07:49:08.099289+00'),
	('1a13a742-7d45-483b-8589-de0ac13decf7', 'f221f4f0-193d-4a6a-aa59-de8eebd70258', '100% eco-friendly', 'Our company is committed to being 100% eco-friendly and carbon neutral by 2030.', 'high', 90, 'vague_claim', 'The term ''eco-friendly'' is vague and lacks specific information about the environmental benefits. It does not specify which aspects of the product or company are environmentally friendly.', 'Directive on Empowering Consumers for the Green Transition (2024/825)', 'N/A', 'eu', 'Replace with specific and measurable environmental benefits, supported by evidence.', 'Our company is committed to reducing our carbon footprint by 30% by 2030 through the use of renewable energy sources.', 0, '2026-01-29 12:56:07.582812+00'),
	('18f90100-2628-4b6f-ad68-db0fb6c0eac1', 'f221f4f0-193d-4a6a-aa59-de8eebd70258', 'carbon neutral by 2030', 'Our company is committed to being 100% eco-friendly and carbon neutral by 2030.', 'medium', 65, 'future_promise', 'While a commitment to carbon neutrality is positive, the claim lacks details on how this will be achieved. It needs to specify the scope, methodology, and any reliance on carbon offsetting.', 'Green Claims Code', 'Principle 6', 'uk', 'Provide details on the plan to achieve carbon neutrality, including specific actions and timelines.', 'Our company is committed to achieving carbon neutrality by 2030 through a combination of reducing emissions by X% and investing in certified carbon offset projects.', 1, '2026-01-29 12:56:07.582812+00'),
	('07101537-fec6-4381-b18d-55a614b574e8', 'f221f4f0-193d-4a6a-aa59-de8eebd70258', 'sustainable materials in all our products', 'We use sustainable materials in all our products, making them completely green and environmentally safe.', 'medium', 55, 'vague_claim', 'The term ''sustainable materials'' is vague and doesn''t specify what makes the materials sustainable. It needs to be more specific about the materials used and their environmental benefits.', 'Green Claims Code', 'Principle 2', 'uk', 'Specify the materials used and their specific sustainability attributes (e.g., recycled content, renewable source).', 'We use recycled plastic and sustainably sourced wood in our products, reducing our reliance on virgin materials.', 2, '2026-01-29 12:56:07.582812+00'),
	('ad136906-5fbc-430e-84a5-e264a681cadf', 'f221f4f0-193d-4a6a-aa59-de8eebd70258', 'completely green and environmentally safe', 'We use sustainable materials in all our products, making them completely green and environmentally safe.', 'high', 80, 'vague_claim', 'The terms ''completely green'' and ''environmentally safe'' are overly broad and lack specific, verifiable information. No product is entirely without environmental impact.', 'Directive on Empowering Consumers for the Green Transition (2024/825)', 'N/A', 'eu', 'Avoid absolute claims and focus on specific, measurable environmental improvements.', 'Our products are designed to minimize environmental impact through the use of sustainable materials and reduced energy consumption during manufacturing.', 3, '2026-01-29 12:56:07.582812+00'),
	('fc64e291-82f9-461d-8e37-49c00044640b', 'f221f4f0-193d-4a6a-aa59-de8eebd70258', '100% biodegradable', 'Our packaging is 100% biodegradable and our manufacturing process has zero environmental impact.', 'high', 75, 'unsubstantiated', 'The claim that the packaging is ''100% biodegradable'' requires proof and clarification of the conditions under which it will biodegrade. ''Biodegradable'' can be misleading if it requires specific industrial composting facilities.', 'Green Claims Code', 'Principle 1', 'uk', 'Provide evidence of biodegradability under specific conditions and clarify the timeframe.', 'Our packaging is certified biodegradable under industrial composting conditions according to [certification standard].', 4, '2026-01-29 12:56:07.582812+00'),
	('b75730c7-0381-41cd-99b6-2fb7c3533ad1', 'f221f4f0-193d-4a6a-aa59-de8eebd70258', 'zero environmental impact', 'Our packaging is 100% biodegradable and our manufacturing process has zero environmental impact.', 'high', 95, 'absolute_claim', 'Claiming ''zero environmental impact'' is highly unlikely and almost certainly false. All manufacturing processes have some environmental impact.', 'Green Claims Code', 'Principle 1', 'uk', 'Avoid absolute claims and focus on reducing environmental impact.', 'We are continuously working to reduce the environmental impact of our manufacturing process through energy efficiency and waste reduction initiatives.', 5, '2026-01-29 12:56:07.582812+00'),
	('7f7a2d81-f5d2-44cd-9faa-0c6b58ec5f6e', 'f221f4f0-193d-4a6a-aa59-de8eebd70258', 'all-natural, chemical-free products', 'Join us in saving the planet with our all-natural, chemical-free products that are better for you and the Earth.', 'medium', 60, 'vague_claim', 'The terms ''all-natural'' and ''chemical-free'' can be misleading. Everything is made of chemicals, and ''natural'' does not necessarily mean environmentally friendly. It requires clarification and substantiation.', 'Green Claims Code', 'Principle 2', 'uk', 'Specify which chemicals have been avoided and what makes the ''natural'' ingredients environmentally beneficial.', 'Our products are formulated without parabens, phthalates, and artificial fragrances, using plant-derived ingredients where possible.', 6, '2026-01-29 12:56:07.582812+00'),
